<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880916-0008 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Plantronics Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> PLX </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Plantronics Inc., Santa Cruz, Calif., said that, based on a preliminary count, about 90% of its stock outstanding was tendered in an offer made by a management group seeking to take the company private.    The offer, which expired on midnight Wednesday, called for holders to receive $21 in cash and $4 in subordinated debt. The company said about 5.5 million shares had been tendered in the offer, which was for as many as 5.1 million shares. The maker of telecommunications equipment said payment for the shares would begin in about seven days, subject to determination of the final proration factor. Remaining shares will be exchanged for subordinated debt, the company said. </TEXT></DOC>